<div class="user-info">
	<h1 class="no-margin-top">Profile</h1>
	<h2>{{studentInfo.first_name}} {{studentInfo.last_name}} ({{studentGrade}}th Grade, {{studentInfo.graduation_year}})</h2>
	<img src="{{{studentInfo.google_profile_pic_url}}}" style="width: 110px;" alt="{{studentInfo.first_name}} {{studentInfo.last_name}}'s Profile Picture" />
	<!-- Section 1: General -->
	<div class="user-settings-section">
		<h3 class="no-margin-bottom">General</h3>
		<aside class="user-settings-general-aside"><strong>Changes made in this section will be updated upon change (automatically).</strong></aside>
		<div class="user-settings-group">
			<label for="wants-daily-email">Daily schedule email (coming soon)</label>
			<input type="checkbox" class="user-settings-mutator" data-mutates="wants_daily_email" {{#if studentWantsDailyEmail}}checked{{/if}} />
		</div>
	</div>
	<!-- end Section 1 -->
	<!-- Section 2: Classes -->
	<div class="user-settings-section">
	<h3>Classes</h3>
		<table class="class-entry-table fix-border-radius">
			<tbody></tbody>
		</table>
		<button type="button" class="btn submit-btn" id="update-classes">Update Classes</button>
	</div>
	<!-- end Section 2 -->
	<!-- Section 3: Privacy -->
	<div class="user-settings-section">
		<h3>Privacy</h3>
		<p>In compliance with California privacy laws, Schoop allows students to completely wipe all data stored on our servers, though it may be stored for up to one week in a backup performed by our hosting provider to ensure the safety and security of user data. If you have any issue with this, please <a href="mailto:zstjohn22@windwardschool.org">let me know</a>, and I will try to help you to the best of my ability. <strong>Deleting your account irreversible, and we will not be able to restore your data once you have done so.</strong></p>
		<button type="button" class="btn delete-btn">Delete All Data</button>
	</div>
	<!-- end Section 3 -->
	<!-- Section 4: Download -->
	<div class="user-settings-section">
		<h3>Download Backup</h3>
		<p>You may now download a semi-complete backup of your Schoop account. The current format contains your first name, graduation year, seminar info, and classes in a JSON file. In the future, once I have completed the second version of Schoop, you will most likely be able to download your information from here and transfer it to the new version.</p>
		<a href="/api/download/schoop_account.json" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><button type="button" class="btn download-account-btn">Download Backup</button></a>
	</div>
	<!-- end Section 4 -->
</div>
<!-- special common script for class entry -->
<script src="/js/common/class-entry-common.js"></script>